  <bioghist id="aspace_b6d6c2b6dbe3308927b9a374d4f6ce8b">
    <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
<p>August Gold was a member of the Socialist Party in New York. Gold was active in various local chapters of the Party, the cooperative movement, academic freedom, andother radical movements, mostly in the United States, from the 1930s through the 1960s.</p>  </bioghist>
